{
  "text": "To decide whether to repair or reconstruct the annular ligament remains controversial. Some authors prefer annular ligament reconstruction in every case, however some others stated that the annular ligament reconstruction did not affect the radiocapitellar stability [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Tan et al. [CITATION_4] reported that annular ligament was intact and interposed within the radiohumeral joint in their 35 pediatric cases of Monteggia injury. They advocate the open reduction of the annular ligament in every case [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . In chronic Monteggia lesions, if the annular ligament repair cannot be accomplished, reconstruction should be performed to achieve radiocapitellar joint stability [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
